ingredientsDesc: Ferritin Standards:One vial, 10 mL, labeled A, containing 0 ng/mL and five vials, 0.5 mL each, labeled B-F, containing concentrations of approximately 8, 50, 150, 300, 1000 ng/mL human spleen ferritin in a protein-stabilized buffer with sodium azide as a preservative.Anti-Ferritin [I-125] Reagent:One bottle, 55 mL, containing <10 μCi (370 kBq) of [I-125]-labeled goat anti-huamn spleen ferritin in a protein-stabilized buffer with sodium azide as a preservative. Ferritin Assay Buffer:One bottle, 55 mL, containing a protein-stabilized buffer with sodium azide as a preservative. Anti-Ferritin-Coated Tubes:One hundred (100) polystyrene tubes with goat anti-human spleen ferritin immobilized to the inside wall of each tube.Ferritin Controls:Two vials, 0.5 mL each, Levels I and II, containing low and high concentrations of human spleen ferritin in a protein-stabilized buffer with sodium azide as a preservative.
